==English==
===Etymology===
English colre, from Old French, from Latin cholera, cholera, jaundice, from Greek kholera, from khol, bile

===Pronunciation===
kol'er

===Noun===
# [[anger|Anger]] or [[irritability]].
# One of the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_humours four humors] of ancient physiology. Also known as yellow bile.

